OL,4,CVictims await report into biggest ever
OL,5,CNHS disaster
OL,6,GThe public inquiry into the infected
OL,7,Gblood scandal, known as the biggest
OL,8,Gtreatment disaster in NHS history, is
OL,9,Gdue to publish its findings.
OL,11,FMore than 30,000 people were infected
OL,12,Fwith HIV and hepatitis C from 1970 to
OL,13,F1991 by contaminated blood products
OL,14,Fand transfusions.
OL,16,FAbout 3,000 of them have since died -
OL,17,Fmany haemophiliacs given infected
OL,18,Fblood products as part of their
OL,19,Ftreatment.
OL,21,FPrime Minister Rishi Sunak is expected
OL,22,Fto issue an apology on Monday.
